<Layout title="Safety & Risk Management Assessment Tools" description="Safety and risk management assessment tools used in nursing">
  <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`} class="back-link">← Back to all categories</a>
  <div class="badge">Safety &amp; Risk Management</div>
  <h1>Safety &amp; Risk Management Assessment Tools</h1>
  <p>Standardized tools for patient safety, clinical handoffs, early warning, and risk identification.</p>

  <div class="tool-list">
    <h2>Assessment Tools</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Braden Scale</strong> — Pressure injury risk assessment: Sensory Perception, Moisture, Activity, Mobility, Nutrition, Friction/Shear. Score ≤18 = at risk; guides preventive intervention.</li>
      <li><strong>Morse Fall Scale</strong> — Six-item fall risk tool for hospitalized adults. Score ≥45 = high fall risk; triggers individualized fall prevention protocols.</li>
      <li><strong>WHO Surgical Safety Checklist</strong> — Three-phase perioperative safety verification: Sign In (before anesthesia), Time Out (before incision), Sign Out (before leaving OR). Reduces surgical complications and mortality.</li>
      <li><strong>Time-Out Verification</strong> — Pre-procedure verification of patient identity, procedure, site, laterality, implants, and team concerns; mandatory for all invasive procedures.</li>
      <li><strong>SBAR (Situation, Background, Assessment, Recommendation)</strong> — Structured communication framework for clinical handoffs and escalations; standardizes information transfer to reduce errors.</li>
      <li><strong>I-PASS Handoff Tool</strong> — Illness severity, Patient summary, Action list, Situation awareness, Synthesis by receiver; evidence-based handoff structure reducing medical errors.</li>
      <li><strong>ISBAR</strong> — Identify, Situation, Background, Assessment, Recommendation; extends SBAR with explicit identification component for telephone and escalation communications.</li>
      <li><strong>HEWS (Hospital Early Warning Score)</strong> — Aggregated physiological parameter scoring for detecting deteriorating inpatients; institutional implementation varies; precursor concept to NEWS systems.</li>
      <li><strong>Suicide Risk Formulation Tools</strong> — Structured professional judgment frameworks (C-SSRS, SAFE-T) guiding documentation of suicide risk level, protective factors, and safety planning.</li>
      <li><strong>Elopement Risk Assessment</strong> — Structured identification of patients at risk for leaving against medical advice or wandering; triggers wandering precautions and environmental modifications.</li>
      <li><strong>Brøset Violence Checklist (BVC)</strong> — Six-item short-term violence risk prediction tool for inpatient settings: confusion, irritability, boisterousness, physical threats, verbal threats, attacks on objects.</li>
      <li><strong>Restraint Justification Assessment</strong> — Clinical and ethical evaluation documenting least-restrictive alternatives tried, medical necessity, patient/family communication, and ongoing reassessment per regulatory requirements.</li>
      <li><strong>Latex Allergy Risk Screening</strong> — Pre-procedure questionnaire identifying latex allergy/sensitivity risk factors: prior latex reactions, spina bifida, multiple surgeries, healthcare worker, food allergies (banana, avocado, kiwi).</li>
      <li><strong>Contrast Dye / Iodine Allergy Screening</strong> — Pre-procedure risk assessment for contrast reactions: prior contrast reactions, iodine allergy, seafood allergy, renal function, metformin use; guides premedication and alternative imaging.</li>
      <li><strong>Malignant Hyperthermia Susceptibility Assessment</strong> — Pre-anesthetic screening for MH risk: personal/family MH history, prior adverse anesthetic reactions; CHCT testing referral for high-risk patients.</li>
      <li><strong>Phlebitis Scale (Visual Infusion Phlebitis Score)</strong> — IV site assessment graded 0–5: 0 (no phlebitis), 5 (advanced phlebitis with palpable cord and pyrexia); guides cannula replacement decisions.</li>
      <li><strong>DIVA Score (Difficult Intravenous Access)</strong> — Pediatric difficult IV access prediction: age &lt;1 year, prematurity, history of difficult access, poor peripheral veins; score ≥4 predicts multiple attempts and supports ultrasound use.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Layout>
